          funding lapse in early 2026, which froze nearly $900 million in approved World Cup
          security grants for all 11 U.S. host cities.
        </p>

        <p className="leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Prior to her Cabinet role, Noem served as the{' '}
          <strong>33rd Governor of South Dakota</strong> (2019–2025), where she gained national
          prominence for refusing to impose pandemic lockdowns, signing some of the country&apos;s
